<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1437,1443,1974]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1876,1902]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is being named to honor our colleague Cinthya S.G. Santos, from the Universidade Federal Fluminense, 
<collectingCountry box="[386,457,1911,1937]" name="Brazil" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in recognition of her publications on polychaete taxonomy, and especially for her longlasting friendship with one of us (AER). The epithet is a noun in the genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
