, paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection lastPageId="62" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,1401,2041]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1401,1428]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[353,457,1402,1428]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Holotype</typeStatus>
(UERJ 6043) with body subcylindrical, slightly swollen in median region and mainly posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[289,396,1438,1464]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1590,1615]" captionTargetBox="[173,1418,184,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[170,1418,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 37. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211).A. Complete paratype, dorsolateral view. B. Anterior region, frontal view. C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D–E. Posterior region. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B: 0.3 mm, C, D: 0.2 mm, E: 0.1 mm. (UERJ 6077: A, B, D; UERJ 6953: C, E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335254/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 37A</figureCitation>
). Integument anteriorly and posteriorly opaque, medially transparent, with a few transverse delicate striae, papillae scarce, minute (
<figureCitation box="[591,693,1474,1500]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38B</figureCitation>
), more abundant in posterior region, especially close to anus. Ventrally with a pronounced median groove (
<figureCitation box="[615,718,1510,1536]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,1401,2041]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Prostomium invaginated, rounded, smooth, without cilia (
<figureCitation box="[845,946,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1590,1615]" captionTargetBox="[173,1418,184,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[170,1418,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 37. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211).A. Complete paratype, dorsolateral view. B. Anterior region, frontal view. C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D–E. Posterior region. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B: 0.3 mm, C, D: 0.2 mm, E: 0.1 mm. (UERJ 6077: A, B, D; UERJ 6953: C, E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335254/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 37B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[958,1010,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">38A</figureCitation>
). Prostomium and peristomium fused. Mouth ventral, anchor-shaped, with two dots due to chaetal broken bases when seen frontally (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1335,1582,1608]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1590,1615]" captionTargetBox="[173,1418,184,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[170,1418,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 37. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211).A. Complete paratype, dorsolateral view. B. Anterior region, frontal view. C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D–E. Posterior region. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B: 0.3 mm, C, D: 0.2 mm, E: 0.1 mm. (UERJ 6077: A, B, D; UERJ 6953: C, E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335254/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 37B</figureCitation>
). Nuchal organs not seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,1401,2041]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Body separated into three regions by width of chaetiger and chaetation patterns. Anterior and terminal segments shorter than other segments; anterior and posterior chaetigers twice wider than long, median chaetigers as long as, or up to 1.5x longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[509,649,1726,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38A, G</figureCitation>
). Median segments bi- or tri-annulated, chaetal bundles in longer ring (
<figureCitation box="[160,300,1762,1788]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38B, C</figureCitation>
). Chaetae disposed laterally on anterior and posterior chaetigers, dorsolaterally along median ones (
<figureCitation box="[160,291,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38D, E</figureCitation>
); all low lobes (two specimens regenerating the anterior region with chaetigers narrower than following ones; i.e. 
<date box="[258,286,1834,1860]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">3x</date>
wider than long). Chaetae distributed in three patterns: notopodia with cA/Ac in anterior and posterior regions (
<figureCitation box="[249,387,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38A, G</figureCitation>
), and A/Ac in median region (
<figureCitation box="[726,861,1870,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38D, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,1401,2041]" lastBlockId="62.[151,1437,153,863]" lastPageId="62" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
Chaetigers 1–4 not modified; first 4–5 chaetigers with one capillary and an acicular, both slightly falcate and of similar length; bidentate notoaciculars present in smaller specimens. Median segments with aciculars straight, not sigmoid; notoaciculars more robust than neuroaciculars, slightly curved; capillaries thin, tapered. Parapodia 5–8 to 36(–44) with a single acicular in notopodia and one acicular and one capillary in neuropodia (A/Ac) (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1370,2014,2040]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
B–E). Following 20 chaetigers with cA/Ac, and last 20 chaetigers with 1–2 aciculars and 1–2 capillaries on notopodia and 2–3 aciculars and 2–3 capillars on neuropodia (1–3c1–1A/1–3A1–3c). Chaetae slightly spinulose (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1368,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 38F</figureCitation>
). Last chaetae surpassing pygidial border (
<figureCitation box="[555,659,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1459,1484]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,418,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@54.[170,1418,417,1434]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 34. Laubieriopsis hartmanae (Levenstein, 1970), non-type specimens (LACM 7331-61). A. Complete, dorsal view, asterisk indicates enlarged area (inset: chaetiger 6 showing paired genital papillae). B. Another specimen, anterior end, right lateral view. C. Chaetiger 3, neurochaetae, posterior view. D. Left genital papilla. E. Right genital papilla. F. Posterior region. G. Same, neurochaetae. H. Another specimen, longitudinally sliced showing oocytes (80–100 µm). Scale bars: A: 1 mm (inset: 250 µm.), B: 110 µm, C: 13 µm, D: 70 µm, E 50 µm, F: 360 µm, G: 35 µm, H: 220 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335250/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 34G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,153,863]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Substitute chaetae present, mostly along anterior neuropodia. Interramal papillae pedunculate, rounded, between noto- and neuropodia or slightly closer to notopodia than neuropodia, apparently with a terminal pore (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="61.[151,250,1115,1140]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetId="figure@61.[170,1418,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 38. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211). A. Complete, oblique lateral view (smaller letters indicate following objects). B. Anterior region, dorsolateral view. C. Anterior chaetigers, oblique lateral view. D. Median chaetigers, latero ventral view. E. Anterior chaetiger, close-up of notochaetae and interramal papilla. F. Last chaetigers before posterior swollen region. G. Second chaetiger, tip of notochaeta. H. Anterior chaetiger, notochaeta and interramal papilla. I. Posterior region, oblique lateral view. J. Posterior chaetiger interramal papilla. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B, C: 140 µm, D, I: 250 µm, E, H: 30 µm, F: 200 µm, G: 8 µm, J: 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335256/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 38H</figureCitation>
). Genital papillae not seen. Gametes not seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,153,863]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
Pygidium inconspicuous, with a few minute, digitiform or rounded, sessile papillae, close to anus (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1424,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1590,1615]" captionTargetBox="[173,1418,184,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[170,1418,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 37. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211).A. Complete paratype, dorsolateral view. B. Anterior region, frontal view. C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D–E. Posterior region. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B: 0.3 mm, C, D: 0.2 mm, E: 0.1 mm. (UERJ 6077: A, B, D; UERJ 6953: C, E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335254/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Figure 37D</figureCitation>
). Free-living.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,153,863]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,312,440,467]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Variation</emphasis>
. Some larger specimens with posterior region bulbous and robust aciculars surpassing pygidial margin, forming a chaetal cage. It is possible that this species uses the posterior region of body to anchor in the sediment; as suggested by the fact that two specimens were regenerating the anterior region. In a small 
<typeStatus box="[1294,1390,513,539]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">paratype</typeStatus>
(39 chaetigers; UERJ 1380), probably a juvenile, chaetae are very long and robust, especially on last chaetigers (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1590,1615]" captionTargetBox="[173,1418,184,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@60.[170,1418,181,1565]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 37. Riseriopsis santosae n. sp., paratype (ECOSUR 211).A. Complete paratype, dorsolateral view. B. Anterior region, frontal view. C. Anterior region, dorsal view. D–E. Posterior region. Scale bars: A: 0.7 mm, B: 0.3 mm, C, D: 0.2 mm, E: 0.1 mm. (UERJ 6077: A, B, D; UERJ 6953: C, E)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335254/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 37C, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,153,863]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,621,647]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo, 2019" authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo" authorityYear="2019" box="[325,557,622,647]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fauveliopsidae" genus="Riseriopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="santosae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[325,557,622,647]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Riseriopsis santosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[566,629,621,647]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Thiel, Purschke &amp; Boggemann" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[760,881,621,647]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fauveliopsidae" genus="Riseriopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis box="[760,881,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">R. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because they are free living, and their posterior chaetigers have hyaline chaetae. They differ by the number of chaetigers, and by chaetal patterns in medial chaetigers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,153,863]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
In 
<taxonomicName authority="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo, 2019" authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo" authorityYear="2019" box="[232,364,730,755]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fauveliopsidae" genus="Riseriopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="santosae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[232,364,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">R. santosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[373,436,729,755]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the body has 37–88 chaetigers, and only one acicular per bundle in medial notopodia, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Thiel, Purschke &amp; Boggemann" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[249,367,765,791]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fauveliopsidae" genus="Riseriopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis box="[249,367,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">R. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 15–31 chaetigers, and one acicular and one capillary per bundle in medial notopodia. In addition, 
<taxonomicName authority="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo, 2019" authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo" authorityYear="2019" box="[231,360,802,827]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fauveliopsidae" genus="Riseriopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="santosae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[231,360,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">R. santosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[367,427,801,827]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is a shelf species whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Zhadan &amp; Rizzo" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Thiel, Purschke &amp; Boggemann" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[727,845,801,827]" class="Polychaeta" family="Fauveliopsidae" genus="Riseriopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis box="[727,845,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">R. confusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is abyssal.
</paragraph>
